reviewText:
George McMullen was both an astonishing and good man. At this conference I asked one of IRVA's founders, who among the many psychics he had worked with was the most accurate at what they did. He answered that George, in his day, was one the best he'd ever worked with. I was honored to be among George's audience when he gave this address, which might have been his last public address to his peers before he crossed over the following June.

George's stories and experiences are always fascinating and astounding, and these were no different for me.
